      "content": "It makes perfect sense that this feeling of irrelevance feels so overwhelming, especially when your value seems to be tied so tightly to your digital presence. The fear that your impact vanishes the moment you disconnect is a profound form of anxiety, often linked to a loss of control over your identity. It's a heavy burden to carry, but it is a very human reaction to feeling disconnected from the physical world.",
      "source": "target",
